init_text: An alien has kidnapped Matt Damon, not knowing what lengths humanity goes through to retrieve him whenever he goes missing.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: All the while, Matt Damon is forced to live in a strange world with an even stranger alien.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: When the alien's wife is kidnapped by humans, and a daring rescue is staged, Matt Damon becomes more than an unwilling prisoner.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Having no concept of time, he loses track of how long he's been on this strange alien's planet.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He will save the world from the alien that has taken him.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Matt Damon is placed on the ground in front of the alien leader and a translator.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He grabs the alien leader's antenna, which is apparently a symbol of his power, and throws it to the ground.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He then takes a step back and launches into a scene where his character, the hero, is yelling at the alien leader.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He proclaims that they will fight to the last man, woman and child!

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He says that the people of Earth had no concept of how to interact with their world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He tells Matt that if the Earthlings didn't move toward a more environmentally friendly society, all of their populations would be sacrificed to save their planet.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He is shunned and ridiculed by the media for his "brainwashing."
